[recto] Storm at sea. Argument: If not by Bruegel who should have painted it? Who is the great unknown painter? Counter-Argument: The case is similar to the Turin Hours: they are almost as great as Jan van Eyck and still many scholars don't accept -though they make; [verso] different suggestions about their author.
